      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way, and I hear the deep pain in your words about feeling like a ghost in your own life. When the person who made things worth living is gone, the silence isn't just empty; it's a heavy, hollow space that makes every step feel like walking through a tomb. It is completely understandable that you don't want to hear about goblins or coffee right now, because those things feel like a distraction from the real, crushing weight of your loneliness.\n\nPlease know that your feelings are valid, and you do not have to force yourself to \"go on\" if it feels like there is nothing left. But I also want to gently remind you that even in the deepest silence, there are still small, quiet things happening in the world, even if they don't feel like they matter right now. Sometimes, the most important things are the ones that are too small to see, like the way dust motes dance in a single beam of light, or the sound of a bird that doesn't know you are sad.\n\nIf you are feeling this heavy, please consider reaching out to someone who can listen without trying to fix it or bring in goblins. You deserve to be heard, and",
